<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>P&amp;L Reconciliation V12</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ url_for('static', filename='style.css') }}" />
</head>
<body>
<div id="loginScreen" class="login-screen">
  <div class="login-card">
    <div class="login-brand">AMCO IQ</div>
    <h1>P&amp;L Reconciliation V12</h1>
    <div class="login-sub">Please sign in to access the reconciliation workspace.</div>
    <div class="login-form">
      <label class="login-label" for="loginUsername">Username</label>
      <input id="loginUsername" class="login-input" type="text" autocomplete="username" placeholder="Enter username" />

      <label class="login-label" for="loginPassword">Password</label>
      <input id="loginPassword" class="login-input" type="password" autocomplete="current-password" placeholder="Enter password" />

      <button id="loginBtn" class="btn login-btn" type="button">Log in</button>
      <div id="loginStatus" class="status"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="appShell" class="page" style="display:none">
  <section class="hero hero-with-actions">
    <div>
      <h1>P&amp;L Reconciliation V12</h1>
      <div class="sub">V12 aligns SAP BFC and OneStream at the same OS Level 2 P&amp;L line using the uploaded raw files, the BFC to OS mapping, and the hierarchy reference. The logic is entity-agnostic and can be reused across entities with the same file structure.</div>
    </div>
    <button id="logoutBtn" class="btn secondary" type="button">Log out</button>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>SAP BFC Raw Data</h3>
      <div class="desc">Upload the ERP to SAP BFC raw file.</div>
      <input id="sapFile" class="file-input" type="file" accept=".xlsx,.xls,.csv" />
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>OneStream Raw Data</h3>
      <div class="desc">Upload the ERP to OS raw file.</div>
      <input id="osFile" class="file-input" type="file" accept=".xlsx,.xls,.csv" />
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Entity</h3>
      <div class="desc">Select the entity to tag the result. The backend logic remains reusable across entities with the same file structure.</div>
      <select id="entitySelect" class="file-input">
        <option value="2403" selected>2403</option>
      </select>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
    <div class="desc" style="margin-bottom:0">
      Summary lines in drilldown stay fixed and bold. Only detailed reporting lines expand. Net Finance is kept in drilldown only, while the summary remains clean and uncluttered.
    </div>
    <div class="actions">
      <button id="runBtn" class="btn">Run P&amp;L reconciliation</button>
      <label class="toggle-wrap"><input id="hideZeros" type="checkbox" checked> Hide Zero Lines</label>
    </div>
    <div id="status" class="status"></div>
  </section>

  <section id="resultsPanel" class="panel" style="display:none">
    <div class="panel-head">
      <div>
        <div class="panel-title">P&amp;L reconciliation output</div>
        <div class="panel-sub">Generated from the uploaded raw files, the BFC to OS mapping, and the OS hierarchy reference.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="badge">AMCO IQ</div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
      <div class="meta-row">
        <div class="meta"><div class="k">SAP rows</div><div id="metaSapRows" class="v">-</div></div>
        <div class="meta"><div class="k">OS rows</div><div id="metaOsRows" class="v">-</div></div>
        <div class="meta"><div class="k">GL codes</div><div id="metaGlCodes" class="v">-</div></div>
        <div class="meta"><div class="k">Unmapped GL codes</div><div id="metaUnmapped" class="v">-</div></div>
        <div class="meta"><div class="k">Entity</div><div id="metaEntity" class="v">-</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="summaryTab">Summary</button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="drillTab">Drilldown</button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="debugTab">Debug</button>
      </div>

      <div id="summaryTab" class="tab-pane active">
        <div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr>
          <th>Line item</th><th class="num">SAP BFC</th><th class="num">OneStream</th><th class="num">Difference</th>
        </tr></thead><tbody id="summaryBody"></tbody></table></div>
      </div>

      <div id="drillTab" class="tab-pane">
        <div class="section-note">The drilldown follows the P&amp;L hierarchy in a clean summary-first layout. Main sections stay fixed and bold, while only detailed reporting lines expand.</div>
        <div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr>
          <th>Line item / GL code</th><th>Description</th><th>Currency</th><th class="num">SAP BFC</th><th class="num">OneStream</th><th class="num">Difference</th>
        </tr></thead><tbody id="drillBody"></tbody></table></div>
      </div>

      <div id="debugTab" class="tab-pane">
        <div class="section-note">Use this to review warnings, excluded non-P&amp;L lines, and any codes that did not land on a visible line item.</div>
        <div id="debugBox" class="debug-box"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<div id="overlay" class="overlay">
  <div class="loader">
    <div class="badge" style="margin:0 auto 16px">AMCO IQ</div>
    <div class="loader-title">Processing</div>
    <div class="loader-text">Running P&amp;L reconciliation...</div>
    <div class="bar"><div></div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<script src="{{ url_for('static', filename='app.js') }}"></script>
</body>
</html>
